On 4/18/03 11:44 PM, "Paul Archibald" <androbus(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:

> ok....so I'll be tightening them up 'til I get .006
> space....than tighten up One turn just to be paranoid...a
> complete turn really screws things down a lot!  than after
> determining it's ok, driving it around with a little
> clatter for soome local driving, the next day will tightem
> sown another .25 to .5 turn...depending on where that puts
> things with the valve...right? makes more sense to be
> carefull

The 1.5 turns logic is so: too much and the lifter could bottom out, too
little and the valve seat will get hammered. Without anyone providing data
through experiment at both extremes, 1.5 became the magic number. A quiet
valve train and good compression seem to bear it out.

